This paper deals with secure multicast network coding, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). It also addresses the issue of eavesdropping and security (cs.CR), and the computation of secure communication rates (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes an intermediate model of secure unicast, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SI).
